<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> Foundation for Individual Rights in Education. <a href="http://www.thefire.org/Fire_speech_codes_report_2007.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.thefire.org/Fire_speech_codes_report_2007.pdf" rel="nofollow">Spotlight on Speech Codes 2007: The State of Free Speech on Our Nation's Campuses</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-UNCG-37">^ <a href="#cite_ref-UNCG_37-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-UNCG_37-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-UNCG_37-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-UNCG_37-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> Withers, Lanita. UNCG drops speech-zone charges. <a href="/wiki/News_%26_Record" title="News &amp; Record" class="mw-redirect">News &amp; Record</a>, January 18, 2004. Retrieved from Lexis Nexis on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="12-20"><a href="/wiki/December_20" title="December 20">December 20</a></span>, 2006</li>
